"particle does a hair may do also. A hair is as long as the particle path "
"would be for a particle with a lifetime of 100 frames. Instead of rendering "
"every frame of the particle animation point by point there are calculated "
"control points with an interpolation, the segments."
msgstr "Le chemin complet des particules est calculé en avance. Ainsi "

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:27
msgid "Styling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:29
msgid ""
"The next step is to style the hair. You can change the look of base hairs by "
"changing the :doc:`Physics Settings </physics/particles/emitter/physics/"
"index>`."
msgstr ""
"L'étape suivante est les cheveux. Vous pouvez modifier l'apparence de base "
"en changeant les :doc:`réglages de Physique </physics/particles/emitter/"
"physics/index>`."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:32
msgid ""
"A more advanced way of changing the hair appearance is to use :doc:`Children "
"</physics/particles/emitter/children>`. This adds child hairs to the "
"original ones, and has settings for giving them different types of shapes."
msgstr ""
"Une manière plus avancée de modifier l'apparence des cheveux est d'utiliser "
"des :doc:`Enfants </physics/particles/emitter/children>`. Ceci ajoute des "
"cheveux d'enfant aux originaux, et a des réglages pour leur donner "
"différents types de formes."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:36
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You can also interactively style hairs in :doc:`Particle Edit Mode </physics/"
"particles/mode>`. In this mode, the particle settings become disabled, and "
"you can comb, trim, lengthen, etc. the hair curves."
msgstr ""
"Vous pouvez aussi interactivement les cheveux dans le :doc:`Particle Edit "
"Mode </physics/particles/mode>`. Dans ce mode, les réglages de particule "
"deviennent désactivés, et vous pouvez peigner, les courbes de cheveux."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:41
msgid "Animating"
msgstr "Animation"

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:43
msgid ""
"Hair can now be made dynamic using the cloth solver. This is covered in the :"
"ref:`Hair Dynamics <hair-dynamics>` page."
msgstr ""
"Les cheveux peuvent maintenant être en utilisant le **. Ceci est couvert "
"dans la page :ref:`Hair Dynamics <hair-dynamics>`."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:48
msgid "Rendering"
msgstr "Rendu"

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:50
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Blender can render hairs in several different ways. Materials have a Strand "
"section, which is covered in the materials section in the :doc:`Strands Page "
"</render/blender_render/materials/properties/strands>`."
msgstr ""
"Blender peut faire le rendu des cheveux de plusieurs manières différentes. "
"Les matériaux ont une section *Strand*, qui est couverte dans la section "
"*Materials* dans la :doc:`page Strands </render/blender_render/materials/"
"properties/strands>`."

#: ../../manual/physics/particles/hair/introduction.rst:54
msgid ""
"Hair can also be used as a basis for the :doc:`Particle Instance Modifier </"
"modeling/modifiers/simulate/particle_instance>`, which allows you to have a "
"mesh be deformed along the curves, which is useful for thicker strands, or "
"things like grass, or feathers, which may have a more specific look."
msgstr ""
"Les cheveux peuvent aussi être utilisés pour le :doc:`Modificateur Particle "
"Instance </modeling/modifiers/simulate/particle_instance>`, qui vous permet "
"d'avoir un maillage déformé le long des courbes, ce qui est utile pour des "
"brins épais, ou des choses comme l'herbe, ou des plumes, qui peuvent avoir "
"une apparence plus spécifique. "
